         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Ministry of State. ¶ Madrid 10 March 1872. ¶  ¶ My Dear Sir: I have the honour of making known to you that H. M. the King, my august Sovereign, has deigned to nominate you by Decree of this date ordin...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">72.03.10a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Bonifacio de Blas Muñoz</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M200a.12, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS is a printed document on which the rank and Order and M's name have been entered by hand.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Ministerio de Estado.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">Madrid 10 de Marzo de 1872.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Muy Señor mio: Tengo la honra de poner en conocimiento de V. que S. M. el Rey, mi augusto Soberano, se ha dignado nombrarle por Decreto esta fecha <seg style="">Comendador</seg> ordinario de la Real Orden de <seg style="">Isabel la Católica</seg>, cuyo Titulo tendré la satisfaccion de remitir á V. oportunamente.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Aprovecho esta ocasion para ofrecer á V. las seguridades de mi distinguida consideracion.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Bonifo<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Final 'o' superscript; contraction for Bonifacio.</p>
               </note> de Blas</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Al Baron Fernando de Müller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ministry of State.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Madrid 10 March 1872.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My Dear Sir: I have the honour of making known to you that H. M. the King, my august Sovereign, has deigned to nominate you by Decree of this date ordinary Commander of the Royal Order of Isabel la Católica, the diploma of which I shall have the satisfaction of sending you in due course.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Amadeo I, King of Spain, to M, 18 March 1872 (in this edition as 72-03-18b).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I take this opportunity to offer you the assurance of my distinguished consideration.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Bonif[aci]o de Blas</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">To Baron Ferdinand von Mueller</p>
